# {{PROJECT}}-core

Backend API for {{PROJECT}}. {{PROJECT_DESCRIPTION}}

This service owns the product-specific domain. Auth, email, and asset endpoints live in the shared `user-service` (not in this repo).

## Quick start

```bash
{{PACKAGE_MANAGER}} install
cp .env.example .env
{{PACKAGE_MANAGER}} run dev          # http://localhost:3000
```

Hot reload via `nodemon` + `tsx`. Source edits in `src/` restart the process.

To run the full stack locally (with the user-service + nginx in front), use the deployment dev compose instead:

```bash
cd ../{{PROJECT}}-deployment/dev
docker compose up
```

That stack serves http://localhost:3030 with nginx fronting both services.

## Project structure

```
src/
├── index.ts              # process entry — db.connect(), listen(), graceful shutdown
├── app.ts                # express app construction (no listen) — also imported by integration tests
├── config.ts             # env validation (Joi) + typed config export
├── logger.ts             # pino, JSON-structured for Loki
├── openapi.ts            # swagger-jsdoc aggregator
├── db/                   # DB driver init + ping
{{#REDIS}}├── cache/                # redis client init + ping
{{/REDIS}}├── errors/
│   ├── api-error.ts      # ApiError(code, message, statusCode, details?)
│   └── codes.ts          # SCREAMING_SNAKE error-code taxonomy
├── lib/
│   ├── serialize.ts      # Mongo _id → id mapping
│   └── ulid.ts           # newId(prefix) — time-sortable, prefixed
├── middleware/
│   ├── request-id.ts     # ULID per request, echoed in X-Request-Id
│   ├── api-version.ts    # reads {{API_VERSION_HEADER}} header
│   ├── jwt-verify.ts     # requireAuth + requireRole
│   ├── validate.ts       # Joi schema runner
│   ├── error-handler.ts  # converts thrown errors → flat error JSON
│   └── not-found.ts      # 404 catch-all
├── routes/
│   ├── index.ts          # mounts feature routers
│   └── health.ts         # /health (liveness) + /health/ready (DB ping)
├── modules/              # feature modules go here (see "Adding a feature" below)
└── types/
    ├── express.d.ts      # augments Request with requestId, apiVersion, user
    └── env.d.ts          # augments process.env
```

## Adding a feature

Create `src/modules/<feature>/`:

```
<feature>.controller.ts   # HTTP handlers — throw ApiError, never raw try/catch
<feature>.service.ts      # business logic — pure where possible
<feature>.repository.ts   # DB access — the ONLY layer that touches the driver
<feature>.routes.ts       # express Router with Swagger JSDoc
<feature>.schema.ts       # Joi validation
index.ts                  # public exports
```

Then mount it in `src/routes/index.ts`:

```ts
import { router as itemRouter } from '../modules/item/item.routes';
apiRouter.use('/items', itemRouter);
```

Controllers throw `ApiError`; the error-handler middleware converts to the flat error JSON. Never write `try/catch` around the whole controller — only catch specific errors you can handle.

## API contract (summary)

- Base path: `{{API_BASE}}` (no URL versioning)
- Required header: `{{API_VERSION_HEADER}}: {{API_VERSION_DEFAULT}}`
- Success body: the resource directly (no envelope, no `data` wrapper)
- List body: `{ items, nextCursor, hasMore, limit }`
- Error body (flat): `{ code, message, details?, requestId? }`
- HTTP status is the source of truth for success/failure

Full contract: `../docs/API_CONTRACT.md`.

